<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/9–644</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Deputy Director of the Office of European
                                Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in
                                Canada</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-06">September 6, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Ray</hi>: As you know, I pointed out to Admiral
                            Leahy the importance we attach, with a view to your position in Canada,
                            to your presence for at least a part of the forthcoming talks at Quebec.
                            The Admiral fully understood and telephoned me this afternoon to say
                            that he had discussed the matter with the President, and that the
                            President <pb facs="0093" n="39" xml:id="pg_39"/> wishes you to come to
                            see him at Quebec on the 11th or 12th of September. When you arrive, I
                            suggest that you get in touch again with Admiral Leahy.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Hastily,</p>
                        <p>As ever,</p>
                        <closer><signed>H F[<hi rend="smallcaps">reeman</hi>] M[<hi rend="smallcaps">atthews</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>